$ userinit.exe

`userinit.exe` is the default executable that *Winlogon*  runs when a → Windows/user-account[user] logs into → Windows.

`userinit.exe`
  • runs logon scripts
  • reestablishes network connections and
  • starts the *shell* (by default → Windows/dirs/Windows/explorer_exe[`explorer.exe`])



sa:
  The default value of → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Microsoft/Windows-NT/CurrentVersion/Winlogon#reg-userinit[`Userinit`] under
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Microsoft/Windows-NT/CurrentVersion/Winlogon[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon`]
  points to `userinit.exe.`

